.show()"],"metadata":{"id":"ieIlvexdpx0R","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1780828124300,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":339,"user":{"displayName":"Sarthak Singh","userId":"13958553251603189397"}},"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":436},"outputId":"dddd9c8f-5565-43dc-e178-1cdc2726e67d"},"execution_count":43,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 1. Why did you pick the specific chart?\n","I chose a dual line chart with a 50% benchmark line to clearly show when and where completion rate falls below acceptable level"],"metadata":{"id":"5CtXJ_u9qUsP"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##### 2. What is/are the insight(s) found from the chart?\n","Airport completion rate drops below 20% during Night hours. City maintains slightly better rate throughout the day."],"metadata":{"id":"BtGtUyZMqZzj"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## **5. Solution to Business Objective**"],"metadata":{"id":"JcMwzZxoAimU"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#### What do you suggest the client to achieve Business Objective ?\n","Explain Briefly."],"metadata":{"id":"8G2x9gOozGDZ"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["I recommend the following remedies to Uber based on my analysis:\n","1. Driver Incentives for Early Morning — Uber should provide surge pricing and bonus incentives to drivers who accept rides between 5 and 9 AM, particularly from city pickup points, as cancellations are at their highest during this time.\n","2.  Night Shift Drivers — The issue of no cars available is at its worst at night and at the airport. In order to guarantee car availability between 10 PM and 4 AM, Uber should hire dedicated night shift drivers with additional compensation.\n","3. Airport Dedicated Fleet — Since Airport has the worst completion rate of 41%, Uber should maintain a dedicated pool of drivers at Airport during early morning hours when flights arrive.\n","4. Penalty for Cancellations - In order to lower the cancellation rate during early morning and morning slots, drivers who regularly cancel during peak hours should be subject to fines.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"pASKb0qOza21"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Conclusion**"],"metadata":{"id":"gCX9965dhzqZ"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["I examined 6745 Uber ride requests for this EDA project and discovered that 58% of them were unfilled. Early morning and nighttime hours are when the supply-demand mismatch is at its worst. Airport pickup locations see the most number of No Cars Available problems, whereas city pickup locations experience the highest number of driver cancellations. Uber can greatly increase the completion rate, which will increase revenue and enhance customer happiness, by addressing these two underlying issues through driver incentives and night shift deployment."],"metadata":{"id":"Fjb1IsQkh3yE"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### ***Hurrah! You have successfully completed your EDA Capstone Project !!!***"],"metadata":{"id":"gIfDvo9L0UH2"}}]}